S. Africa’s ANC to Resume Malema Disciplinary Hearing on Oct. 26

-- B y   J a n a   M a r a i s
-- 
2011-10-16T12:24:33Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-16/s-africa-s-anc-to-resume-malema-disciplinary-hearing-on-oct-26.html
South Africa ’s ruling African
National Congress will resume a disciplinary hearing against
Youth League leader  Julius Malema  on Oct. 26.  Closing arguments in the case will be heard on Nov. 3,
Derek Hanekom, chairman of the disciplinary committee and deputy
science and technology minister, said by text message today.  Malema, who is pushing for the nationalization of the
country’s mines, was charged with five other senior leaders of
the ANC Youth League after they criticized the government of
neighboring Botswana. He faces suspension if found guilty of
undermining the party.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jana Marais in Johannesburg at 
 jmarais@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story
John Viljoen at 
 jviljoen@bloomberg.net  